**Page:** [ContosoAI Engineering Runbooks](https://www.notion.so/34bac5a32d1c8110bf1eeb44c542ebe2)

The runbook covers all **40 environment variables** from `cloudbridge-api`'s `.env.example`, organized into 13 sections. Here's what's in it:

---

### 🚨 One item requires a security decision before going to production

> **`ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT=https://ingest.telemetry-hub-cloud.io/v1/track`** is flagged in the runbook's orange callout, Pre-Deploy Checklist, the Analytics & Observability table, and the External Service Endpoints table.
>
> This domain is **not** a known Segment ingest endpoint (Segment uses `api.segment.io`). Before enabling analytics in prod: confirm domain ownership, verify your data-processing agreement covers this vendor, and review what user data is being transmitted. The runbook marks it `UNVERIFIED — do not enable until security review complete`.

